The article is a transcript of President Trump's remarks at the 68th annual National Prayer Breakfast. He discusses topics such as the state of the nation, the economy, religious freedom, and the protection of faith communities. He also mentions specific instances of religious persecution and highlights the importance of faith and prayer in American society. The President emphasizes his administration's efforts to defend religious liberty and support persecuted Christians around the world. He concludes by expressing gratitude to the audience and reaffirming the nation's commitment to religious freedom and the protection of all religions.